snippet.title: ACLU of Oregon 2020 Membership Conference
snippet.description: Learn about the fight ahead from ACLU staffers including ACLU National Chief Equity and Inclusion Officer, Amber Hikes. And then hear from our keynote speaker, educator, writer, public scholar and spoken word artist, Walidah Imarisha. Imarisha grounds us in Oregon’s Black History by examining institutional white supremacy and centering the resistance of Black communities and other communities of color as active change makers. The keynote highlights how history, politics, and culture have shaped—and will continue to shape—the landscape not only for Black Oregonians, but all Oregonians.
